1
00:00:08,710 --> 00:00:12,190
- Who are you?
- It's been a while, Ms. Hong Yi Yeong.

2
00:00:12,190 --> 00:00:16,900
You got prettier over the past year. Your life must be good.

3
00:00:18,790 --> 00:00:24,300
Do you know me? How do you know me?

4
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:27,940
What do you mean "how"? I'm disappointed.

5
00:00:27,940 --> 00:00:31,460
We dodged a bullet together a year ago.

6
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:36,580
We dodged a bullet together? What do you mean?

7
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:41,050
You have a very innocent face.

8
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:46,030
We met here a year ago. Don't you remember?

9
00:00:59,690 --> 00:01:03,170
Did you come here on that day?

10
00:01:03,170 --> 00:01:08,010
Did you see me here?

11
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:14,170
Your memory is coming back now. That's right, I met you here.

12
00:01:14,170 --> 00:01:18,210
Stay away! Stay away! Stay away!

13
00:01:22,490 --> 00:01:25,400
Insomniac

14
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:32,350
Mr. Tone-Deaf

15
00:01:32,350 --> 00:01:37,880
The number you have reached is unavailable

16
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:49,240
I won't get closer to you, so just answer my questions.

17
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:54,930
Where did you put the object your boyfriend took?

18
00:01:54,930 --> 00:02:00,510
What object? What object exactly  did my boyfriend take?

19
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:03,990
Oh, right. I knew you wouldn't tell me easily.

20
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:09,790
Considering more important people are desperately looking for it, it must be very important.

21
00:02:09,790 --> 00:02:14,240
I would have hidden it well if I were you, until its value increases.

22
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:19,870
But you should tell me. It wasn't at your house.

23
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:23,100
You broke into my house. Was it you who broke in?

24
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:28,050
I was going to take it and quietly leave, but I couldn't find it.

25
00:02:28,050 --> 00:02:33,770
Where is it? Hurry and tell me before my patience runs out.

26
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:36,610
The object...

27
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:43,410
What exactly is the item  you're looking for? What does it look like?

28
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:48,340
Are you testing my patience now?

29
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:53,770
Don't come near me!

30
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:09,120
Come to think of it, you have some experience.

31
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:13,140
You stabbed your boyfriend that day, right?

32
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:19,160
Did... did you see me stab Ian?

33
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:22,760
That's right. I definitely saw it with my own eyes.

34
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:26,170
Actually, that's the same knife.

35
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:31,100
Did you come here that day with this knife?

36
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:35,530
Are you the one who pointed this knife at me? Are you the owner of this knife?

37
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:41,340
What do you mean? I don't use those toys.

38
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:44,490
- I'm not a kid.
- I'm begging you.

39
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:50,450
Please, tell me what happened here a year ago.

40
00:03:50,450 --> 00:03:56,840
Please. Just tell me what happened that day.

41
00:03:56,840 --> 00:04:02,820
I don't know what you're looking for, but you have to tell me in order to find it, don't you?

42
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:06,140
Do you... not remember that night?

43
00:04:06,140 --> 00:04:10,360
I don't. I don't remember anything.

44
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:14,370
So please just tell me!

45
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:20,070
Oh, so that's how it is.

46
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:22,890
No wonder something was off.

47
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:26,610
So this is why the important people left you alone up to now,

48
00:04:26,610 --> 00:04:29,960
and why you were living like nothing happened.

49
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,210
I understand now.

50
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:43,160
This changes things.

51
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:46,180
- If you are not lying...
- Stay away

52
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:50,160
Yi Yeong? Are you in there? Yi Yeong?

53
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:54,380
- Hong Yi Yeong, are you in there?
- Don't move.

54
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:57,680
Or your pretty neck will be injured.

55
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,760
Hong Yi Yeong?

56
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:08,400
We'll meet again, Hong Yi Yeong.

57
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:18,710
Yi Yeong? What's wrong? What happened?

58
00:05:18,710 --> 00:05:22,640
No, nothing happened. I'm fine.

59
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:39,680
- Can you walk?
- Yes.

60
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:52,340
Mr. Baek's Store

61
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,920
Why are you so lax? Someone almost died.

62
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:03,530
That scumbag followed her and even wounded her neck. How can you say that you don't know where he went?

63
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:06,520
We aren't sure whether it's that bastard or not.

64
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:10,120
I saw the bastard with my own eyes!

65
00:06:11,130 --> 00:06:14,950
- I'm positive it was him.
- It isn't easy to track someone who's off the grid.

66
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:17,840
I'm going to visit his old house. Let's figure things out one by one.

67
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:24,010
Forget it. I don't trust you anymore. Tell me everything you know and I'll look for him.

68
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:51,890
I Wanna Hear Your Song

69
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:57,650
These days, it's a trend for orchestras to choose people who have not majored in music

70
00:06:57,650 --> 00:07:01,140
and plan joint performances and collaborations.

71
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:04,600
The audience wants something that is interesting.

72
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:09,140
He was picked by Maestro Nam himself. He didn't major in music, but he is still very outstanding.

73
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:12,040
You probably will like him.

74
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,940
- Is that him?
- Yes.

75
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:53,840
Not bad. There's a reverberation. What do you think?

76
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:58,620
You're right. I have been watching him since the very beginning.

77
00:07:58,620 --> 00:08:03,620
When he becames famous, the fuss about firing  Gong  Seon Mi will be forgotten.

78
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:07,280
We will be killing two birds with one stone.

79
00:08:08,580 --> 00:08:11,050
What a suck-up.

80
00:08:11,050 --> 00:08:16,880
Give him a pass to the private practice rooms so he can practice in peace. Find him an assistant as well.

81
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:21,840
Make sure he has access to the symphony hall whenever he wants.

82
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:24,870
Take care of it properly.

83
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:38,290
Do you want to go to eat?

84
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:47,010
- What?
- I am going to send a video to your grandmother.

85
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:52,050
- To Bok Bun?
- Yes. I texted the last rehearsal for Scheherazade which I shot.

86
00:08:52,050 --> 00:08:56,440
She said it won't be good for her eyes to watch it on her phone, so she can watch it on a big television screen.

87
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,910
Why would you bother sending a video? She can come see it in person.

88
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:05,010
Come on, why not? I liked this rehearsal so much, it was like an actual performance.

89
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:09,850
She woke up at dawn every day to make noodles and raise you.

90
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:13,930
If she sees this, I think she'll very proud.

91
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:19,000
Where should we go to eat?

92
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,590
Thanks.

93
00:09:30,990 --> 00:09:33,790
Who's there?

94
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:37,290
I think I know. Excuse me.

95
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:43,000
Excuse me! Stop!

96
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,410
You're Yu Da, right?

97
00:09:56,350 --> 00:10:01,530
You took a picture of me with the conductor, right? Why do you hide and do stuff like this?

98
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:06,350
Isn't it cowardly do this under an alias?

99
00:10:06,350 --> 00:10:10,310
Don't hide and ask me directly.

100
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:13,890
I'll tell you everything without hiding anything.

101
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:27,400
General Manager Yun Mi Rae

102
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:49,320
How's your injury? You don't need to go to a hospital?

103
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:54,370
I'm alright. It will heal.

104
00:10:54,370 --> 00:11:00,160
I called a security company. Let's change the door lock today because I'm uneasy.

105
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:08,260
You don't have to worry about this stuff anymore. I'll take care of things.

106
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:12,380
Why are you like this so suddenly?

107
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:18,480
- Like what?
- Saying I don't need to worry and that you'll take care of it. What does that mean?

108
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:21,720
Are you really all right?

109
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,290
What are you talking about?

110
00:11:24,290 --> 00:11:29,060
Are you a robot? Do you have no emotions? Why are you acting as if nothing happened?

111
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:33,110
Only a few hours ago, you were followed by a stranger and almost died in a warehouse.

112
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:37,410
You being alright right now is abnormal, don't you know?

113
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:42,000
Let's talk outside.

114
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:51,350
What happened in the warehouse?

115
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:53,470
Start from the beginning with all the details.

116
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:56,980
What he said to you, and how you got hurt.

117
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:12,950
I thought... he followed me from my house.

118
00:12:12,950 --> 00:12:16,300
As soon I entered the warehouse, he followed in right after.

119
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:19,170
Did you see his face?
- I  couldn't get a good look at it.

120
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:23,900
- It's been a while, Hong Yi Yeong.
- He knew my name.

121
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:28,960
He said we met a year ago in the warehouse.

122
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,890
He definitely said that?

123
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:44,680
And then, he asked where I put the object my boyfriend had.

124
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,880
I was so scared.

125
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:49,200
I was scared, so I...

126
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,940
Don't come close!

127
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:56,690
When I snapped out of it, I was pointing a knife at him.

128
00:12:56,690 --> 00:13:02,450
But he saw that and spoke while smiling.

129
00:13:02,450 --> 00:13:04,760
Did you see?

130
00:13:06,830 --> 00:13:08,390
See me stabbing Kim Ian?

131
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:09,870
Of course.

132
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:12,400
I definitely saw it with my own eyes.

133
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:19,140
Honestly, I was thinking how great it would be if I hadn't stabbed him.

134
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:22,070
That's why I went there.

135
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:23,780
Please, please.

136
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:26,700
I prayed for that as I went.

137
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:30,870
But, in the end...

138
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:37,320
We probably can't date each other anymore, right?

139
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:44,270
I think it'll be best if we aren't too close.

140
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:46,070
Right?

141
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:56,170
Even if we are together, we'll just have bad memories.

142
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:04,110
Please don't be nice to me anymore.

143
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:09,300
I don't have the right to receive that treatment from you.

144
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:19,960
I'll take care of you until the end of the 20th anniversary concert.

145
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,160
At Manager Yun's request.

146
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:26,970
Until the performance, I'll stay next to you and do my best to help you.

147
00:14:26,970 --> 00:14:30,600
Until I figure out why I killed Kim Ian,

148
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:34,660
no matter how disgusted you are, please be patient and deal with me.

149
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:39,680
Once I know that, I'll properly atone for my sins.

150
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:44,330
I wanted to tell you I'm sorry,

151
00:14:44,330 --> 00:14:46,740
but I can't.

152
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:48,770
Because I'm too sorry.

153
00:14:58,110 --> 00:14:59,010
You should leave now.

154
00:14:59,010 --> 00:15:00,600
Goodbye.

155
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,940
Do well.

156
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:08,170
What is this rag doing here.

157
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:09,250
What are you doing?

158
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:12,580
Repeat what you just said.

159
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:16,680
Say it again in front of your mom.

160
00:15:17,380 --> 00:15:19,610
What's wrong with me calling a rag, a rag?

161
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:21,980
Wait, you're not even my teacher anymore.

162
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:25,090
You said you wouldn't pass me because I don't meet the requirements.
(speaking informally)

163
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:27,720
I don't want to learn from you, either.

164
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,300
'Cause you're dirty.

165
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:32,550
You, why are you here?

166
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:33,780
Are you submitting an application here?

167
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,690
And what'll you do with that information?

168
00:15:35,690 --> 00:15:38,910
Ahjumma. Your daughter is at the same level of elementary schoolers.

169
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:40,400
Is college a joke?

170
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,450
Excuse me. Teacher!

171
00:15:42,450 --> 00:15:44,370
Teacher Ha!

172
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:50,720
Why are you speaking such words?

173
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:53,900
These people are my guests. Mind your manners.

174
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:57,270
She's the one who crossed it first.

175
00:15:57,270 --> 00:16:00,620
Did Professor Kang say he'll accept you?

176
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:04,670
How much did you pay him? Tell me, because I think I got the idea already.

177
00:16:05,730 --> 00:16:07,460
Or did you give something else?

178
00:16:07,460 --> 00:16:11,050
Teacher Ha! Are you insane?

179
00:16:11,050 --> 00:16:13,470
What are you trying to say? Do you want to be sued?

180
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:17,580
You should take care of your subordinates properly, Professor.

181
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:23,370
Am I below you? According to whom?

182
00:16:23,370 --> 00:16:25,570
Hey. Move.

183
00:16:25,570 --> 00:16:27,190
Do you not enjoy putting food on the table?

184
00:16:27,190 --> 00:16:32,830
if your daughter gets into this college, I'm going to expose everything.

185
00:16:32,830 --> 00:16:34,720
I'm dirty, so I can do those things pretty well.

186
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:38,310
How dare you threaten us? Go away!

187
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:39,360
You bitch!

188
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,170
- Stop.
- Hey! Hey!

189
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:43,390
Stop it. Stop!

190
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,600
Why are you opening your mouth so carelessly?

191
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:52,180
You have nothing to fear? I thought you'd be useful because you're smart.

192
00:16:52,180 --> 00:16:55,770
You're clueless.

193
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:59,580
Leave. Get lost.

194
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:02,060
I said to get lost.

195
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:09,250
Don't even dream of making a living in this field!

196
00:17:19,950 --> 00:17:21,300
Just wait.

197
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:25,460
No matter what you do, I'll never quit music.

198
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:27,480
It's not in your power.

199
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,730
Music is not in your power.

200
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:37,160
But... how can I pull through?

201
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:46,470
Punk.

202
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,300
Did something happen?

203
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,520
The kids these days are useless.

204
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:55,210
When you codde them, they soon grow up.

205
00:17:55,210 --> 00:17:59,550
You said it was a good idea to continue granting concessions, but that's exactly too...

206
00:18:04,170 --> 00:18:09,670
What's wrong? For the busiest man in the world to come see me.

207
00:18:09,670 --> 00:18:11,150
What happened?

208
00:18:11,150 --> 00:18:16,550
Yun Yeong Gil found me. He threatened me, saying he'll take revenge.

209
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:18,960
Did you order him to say that?

210
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,870
That trash-like bastard. He's doing all sorts of things.

211
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:26,640
He must need money. Since he's going around to people.

212
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:30,660
Make sure he doesn't appear in front of me ever again. It's uncomfortable.

213
00:18:33,620 --> 00:18:37,110
I said it wasn't me.

214
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:41,130
Did you know Kim Ian had an older brother?

215
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,360
What are you talking about now?

216
00:18:47,420 --> 00:18:52,350
When he was young, he had a brother he was separated from. And he's in our orchestra.

217
00:18:52,350 --> 00:18:55,390
In the orchestra? Why?

218
00:18:55,390 --> 00:18:57,740
How did you find out about him?

219
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:02,340
Who is he?

220
00:19:09,990 --> 00:19:11,020
You want coffee?

221
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:13,770
No, it's alright. Do you know if you possibly have more of Ian's things?

222
00:19:13,770 --> 00:19:18,090
I doubt it. You took everything.

223
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:20,390
Just in case, can you look into it?

224
00:19:20,390 --> 00:19:22,770
If there's anything left over, anything's fine, so give it to me right away.

225
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:25,000
Why, what happened?

226
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:28,580
He said he's looking for an object. An object that Ian took.

227
00:19:28,580 --> 00:19:29,920
What did Ian take?

228
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:35,450
He's never even held a water gun and only played the piano. He never said something?

229
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:38,320
No. He saw.

230
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:44,130
He was in the warehouse the day Ian died. It's not a simple hit-and-run.

231
00:19:44,130 --> 00:19:48,070
He's not moving alone, either. There's definitely someone behind him.

232
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:50,790
This is getting more and more complicated.

233
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,940
How's Hong Yi Yeong?

234
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,230
Not good.

235
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:57,990
Until she figures out why she killed Ian she want me to tolerate her.

236
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,260
She will atone for her wrong after that.

237
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:03,560
How far can we trust her words?

238
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,200
We got this from the place where Yun Yeong Gil was staying.

239
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:11,960
It's the moving company he left his luggage with. He must have retrieved them after he was released from prison.

240
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:13,750
You can try meeting them.

241
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:17,140
You have a picture of Yun Yeong Gil, right? Send it to me right away.

242
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:22,030
I'm the one who contacted you.

243
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:26,340
I'm looking for someone. Do you recognize him?

244
00:20:29,010 --> 00:20:31,760
Oh, him. Yes.

245
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,270
About a month ago,

246
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:36,120
he asked me to deliver his stuff which we had in long term storage.

247
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:39,530
Do you perhaps still have his address? The company says they have no records.

248
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,890
Nah, the company won't tell you even if they do.

249
00:20:42,890 --> 00:20:45,830
And he didn't tell us the address to the end.

250
00:20:45,830 --> 00:20:47,830
I don't know if he didn't like being on record,

251
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:51,850
but he called me literally right before he was about to leave.

252
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:54,170
Where was it?

253
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:57,900
It was motel somewhere near Myeongryeon-dong.

254
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:04,890
If you remember the location, could you please contact me right away? I'll compensate you.

255
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:21,070
Who killed  your brother?

256
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:23,930
Someone he loved.

257
00:21:23,930 --> 00:21:27,330
The one who stabbed Ian could be you.

258
00:21:27,330 --> 00:21:30,720
It was someone my brother loved.

259
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,400
You.

260
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,020
Stay back!

261
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:37,120
Oh right, you have some experience.

262
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:40,150
You stabbed your boyfriend that night.

263
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,430
Why?

264
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:49,070
Why did I stab Kim Ian?

265
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:51,870
He was my boyfriend, so why?

266
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:57,330
I need to meet him again.

267
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:01,210
I need to hear for myself what he saw that night.

268
00:22:01,210 --> 00:22:05,960
He will know why  I stabbed Kim Ian.

269
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:08,870
How can I meet him again?

270
00:22:17,630 --> 00:22:19,070
Why am I like this?

271
00:22:19,070 --> 00:22:24,640
Hong Yi Yeong, did you take a class with me at Gyeongsang University in third year?

272
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:27,560
Do you remember the graduate assistant?

273
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:31,170
Do you remember someone named Jang Do Hun?

274
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:37,630
Who?

275
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:40,300
What is it that you remember?

276
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,980
We saw him a few times at university.

277
00:22:44,230 --> 00:22:46,090
Who is it that you're like this?

278
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:52,340
Just for one day, I wish I could live thoughtlessly like you do.

279
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:57,090
How can I help you?

280
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:06,420
Excuse me, is there a professor or teacher assistant named Jang Do Hun?

281
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:09,170
Jang Do Hun?

282
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:11,570
There's no one here with that name.

283
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:13,430
Really?

284
00:23:14,330 --> 00:23:16,000
I'm sorry.

285
00:23:29,490 --> 00:23:34,390
I was going to call you, but I figured you wouldn't answer.

286
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,960
The security compamy called back. He'll come tomorrow.

287
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:43,840
Why? I said I'd do things myself.

288
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:46,760
But you're not. What are you going to do tonight?

289
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:48,440
Are you certain he won't come back?

290
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:50,590
It's too bad if he comes back.

291
00:23:50,590 --> 00:23:52,200
I said I'll deal with it.

292
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:55,720
You don't even know who he is and you'll deal with him yourself?

293
00:23:58,030 --> 00:24:01,480
I just happened to go last time but the next time I might not be there.

294
00:24:02,230 --> 00:24:04,420
It doesn't matter.

295
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:07,330
It matters to me.

296
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:14,460
I don't want you getting hurt.

297
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:20,470
If you get hurt from this, I don't think I'll forgive myself.

298
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:32,130
You don't need to take responsibility. It's my problem.

299
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:33,320
It's my problem, too.

300
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:38,130
And... it's not about responsibility.

301
00:24:38,130 --> 00:24:40,790
If not, then why?

302
00:24:48,850 --> 00:24:49,550
Yeah?

303
00:24:49,550 --> 00:24:51,290
Where are you? Father fainted.

304
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:53,500
Come to the hospital right away.

305
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:56,870
Why, who was it?

306
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,670
My uncle fainted.

307
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:29,480
Did something big happen for you all to be standing here?

308
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,990
It's just my appendix.

309
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:34,020
We came to watch an old man's appendix explode.

310
00:25:34,020 --> 00:25:36,730
Since you're joking around, you seem awake.

311
00:25:36,730 --> 00:25:41,310
Of course. You would be bored without me.

312
00:25:42,630 --> 00:25:46,590
This man. Can you joke at a time like this?

313
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:50,600
There's so much to do, but your timing's spectacular.

314
00:25:51,250 --> 00:25:53,170
I'm going to be drowned in work.

315
00:25:53,170 --> 00:25:57,380
Is that why you were crying about him dying and whatnot?

316
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:00,350
The surgery went well.

317
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:02,960
You'll recover quickly, so just wait a few days.

318
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,620
Alright.

319
00:26:04,620 --> 00:26:09,860
Will I die from my appendix? You go back to work.

320
00:26:09,860 --> 00:26:12,050
You too, Yi Yeong.

321
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:18,150
Why do you look more like a patient than I do? And what's with your neck?

322
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:22,860
She said she scratched it while running. I don't know what that young one's doing with her eyes.

323
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:25,090
You both should get going so your dad can sleep.

324
00:26:25,090 --> 00:26:26,770
Sleep.

325
00:26:26,770 --> 00:26:30,310
I'm on the night shift. I'll call you when I'm off.

326
00:26:30,310 --> 00:26:33,170
I'll come back tomorrow, Uncle.

327
00:26:33,170 --> 00:26:34,560
Go.

328
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,940
Let's talk.

329
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:51,130
Why did you come in Jang Yun's car? Were you with him?

330
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:54,340
Didn't I tell you not to be close with him?

331
00:26:54,340 --> 00:26:57,710
It wasn't on purpose. We met coincidentally in front of our houses.

332
00:26:57,710 --> 00:27:01,440
Get out of the house immediately. Until you get your stuff out, stay at our house.

333
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,240
Okay?

334
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:05,000
There's no need for that.

335
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,320
I'm not going to meet him anymore.

336
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,620
I won't cross paths with him.

337
00:27:12,070 --> 00:27:15,120
How did you  hurt your neck? Don't lie to me.

338
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:16,470
Tell me everything truthfully.

339
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:19,590
I went to the warehouse I went with Jang Yun.

340
00:27:19,590 --> 00:27:23,110
It's a very old warehouse so I got hurt when I didn't look where I was going.

341
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:24,920
Are you crazy? Why would you go there?

342
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:26,750
I went because I thought I should.

343
00:27:26,750 --> 00:27:29,430
He said I killed Kim Ian.

344
00:27:29,430 --> 00:27:31,680
I need to know why, at least.

345
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,200
What do you mean, you killed him?

346
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:36,190
I could have killed him.

347
00:27:37,610 --> 00:27:39,940
What if I did?

348
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:44,540
Just act as if I didn't do it, as if I don't remember?

349
00:27:44,540 --> 00:27:47,690
Just pretend you don't know.

350
00:27:48,490 --> 00:27:51,050
It's not something for you to get involved in.

351
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:12,720
I was working overtime when you called. I have to get back soon.

352
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:16,950
I told you why over the phone. I'll be direct.

353
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:22,900
Funny, right?

354
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:26,120
I feel the same way. I didn't think I'd be like this.

355
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:29,380
But I can't think of anything else.

356
00:28:30,420 --> 00:28:34,180
I didn't meet that prosecutor for money.

357
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:36,920
Well, it wasn't for love, was it?

358
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,040
Love?

359
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:41,700
He had a bit of money, so I just played around with him.

360
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:46,270
He's super boring so I won't meet him again. You can just go.

361
00:28:46,270 --> 00:28:50,030
Then can you sign here instead?

362
00:28:50,030 --> 00:28:52,330
Memorandum

363
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:55,260
No! Why would I sign something like this?

364
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:57,140
Unni, you shouldn't live like this.

365
00:28:57,140 --> 00:29:00,460
Just call the higher-up ahjumma who sent you on this errand.

366
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:04,880
My morals are preventing me from seeing her husband again.

367
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:08,160
Pick it up before you go.

368
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:11,880
What did you say?

369
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,100
Are you deaf?

370
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:17,460
I said to pick up the money and put it here before you leave.

371
00:29:17,460 --> 00:29:19,730
Are you insane?

372
00:29:25,070 --> 00:29:27,710
Yeah. I'm insane after seeing you.

373
00:29:27,710 --> 00:29:29,540
Is money a joke to you?

374
00:29:29,540 --> 00:29:33,220
This money is something I earned while working myself to the bones.

375
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:35,290
It's not money for you to treat so carelessly.

376
00:29:35,290 --> 00:29:37,870
Pick it up. Now.

377
00:29:40,470 --> 00:29:43,940
How many times did you sleep with him? I heard you got a purse too.

378
00:29:43,940 --> 00:29:47,110
What did you get? I'll tell everything to your company.

379
00:29:47,110 --> 00:29:51,450
Does your mom know? That you're sleeping with a married man?

380
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:56,540
Hey. Don't act noble or clean.

381
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:59,980
My money is cleaner than you.

382
00:30:01,870 --> 00:30:03,870
Pick it up, already.

383
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,250
Now!

384
00:30:32,270 --> 00:30:35,450
I thought you were leaving early because you had to do something.

385
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:40,180
I'm back from doing that something. You're still here at this time.

386
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:41,930
Yeah.

387
00:30:46,650 --> 00:30:50,850
I have two and a half hours until my lesson.

388
00:30:50,850 --> 00:30:53,070
Want to eat together?

389
00:31:08,790 --> 00:31:12,440
Mi Rae. What's wrong?

390
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,910
Did something happen?

391
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:21,450
Why are you like this?

392
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,610
Stop crying.

393
00:31:27,050 --> 00:31:28,850
Mi Rae.

394
00:32:03,070 --> 00:32:05,290
What could it be?

395
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:08,790
The object Kim Ian took.

396
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:11,690
Should I have asked for details?

397
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:19,050
I hope I will be accepted.
You can do  it!

398
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:25,420
I doubt Su Yeong has my things.

399
00:32:36,260 --> 00:32:37,770
What's this?

400
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:41,590
Why is this here?

401
00:32:52,290 --> 00:32:54,170
2018.08 Yi Yeong

402
00:32:54,170 --> 00:32:56,860
It's my folder.

403
00:32:58,990 --> 00:33:00,750
2018.08.22

404
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:04,320
Unni was hiding all of this?

405
00:33:12,410 --> 00:33:14,430
Did you sleep well yesterday?

406
00:33:14,430 --> 00:33:19,320
Starting today, we're going to film the conversations you and I have.

407
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:23,590
It's like a regular counseling session, so you can relax.

408
00:33:26,860 --> 00:33:31,100
- A knife?
- What kind of knife?

409
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:38,430
The one that comes out a lot in movies. A switchblade knife.

410
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:41,590
But,

411
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:45,990
but the blood on my hands...

412
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,890
There was blood on my hands.

413
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,730
On my hands.
